# Example / legacy tfvars for the sound-light infrastructure.
#
# Public inputs (project, environment, region, Google client id, …) now live in
# `config/shared.json` at the repo root — Terraform reads that file via
# locals.tf, and the Vite SPA reads the same file via src/config.ts.
#
# You normally do NOT need a terraform.tfvars. Edit config/shared.json instead,
# then `terraform apply` (which also refreshes src/config.generated.json).
